5️⃣ How app.py connects with home.html
Flow:
Browser
   │
   │  GET /
   ▼
Flask Route "/"
   │
   │ return render_template("home.html")
   ▼
templates/home.html
   │
   ▼
Browser shows page
.........................
So connection is:
Route "/"  → render_template("home.html")

...............................................................................................
6️⃣ Passing Data to Template
We can send variables from Python to HTML.
.................................
               Example in app.py
from flask import Flask, render_template

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return render_template("home.html", name="Anand")

app.run(debug=True)
......................
         home.html
<h1>Welcome {{ name }}</h1>

Output:
Welcome Anand

